"scripts": {
// ----------------------------------------------------------
// DEVELOPMENT
// ----------------------------------------------------------

// Fast development mode (recommended 90% of the time)
// Use when actively coding UI/features and want quick reloads.
"dev": "next dev --turbo",

// Strict development mode (run checks BEFORE starting dev)
// Use when starting a new feature or before merging code.
// This will stop if TypeScript or ESLint has errors.
"dev:checked": "npm run predev && next dev --turbo",

// Runs type checking + linting before dev:checked
"predev": "npm run type-check && npm run lint",

// ----------------------------------------------------------
// BUILD & START (Production)
// ----------------------------------------------------------

// Creates a production build (fails if TS/ESLint errors in prod)
// Run this before deploying.
"build": "next build",

// Start the production server (after build)
"start": "next start",

// ----------------------------------------------------------
// TYPE CHECKING
// ----------------------------------------------------------

// Run full TypeScript check once
// Use before commit, before build, or when fixing TS errors.
"type-check": "tsc --noEmit",

// Real-time TS checker ‚Äî shows errors while you code.
// Run this in a second terminal if you want continuous feedback.
"type-check:watch": "tsc --noEmit --watch",

// ----------------------------------------------------------
// LINTING
// ----------------------------------------------------------

// Check all files for ESLint errors (does NOT auto-fix)
// Use before commit or before opening a PR.
"lint": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx",

// Automatically fix all possible ESLint issues
// Use when your code gets messy or after large refactors.
"lint:fix": "eslint . --ext .ts,.tsx,.js,.jsx --fix",

// ----------------------------------------------------------
// FULL CODE QUALITY CHECK
// ----------------------------------------------------------

// Runs TypeScript + ESLint together
// Use before pushing to GitHub or before deployment.
"check": "npm run type-check && npm run lint"
}

When to run which command (simple guide)
üî• Daily development
npm run dev

üîí When you want to ensure your code is clean before starting dev
npm run dev:checked

üì¶ Before deployment (very important)
npm run check
npm run build

üßë‚Äçüíª Before pushing a commit or creating a Pull Request
npm run check

üëÄ Continuous TypeScript error checking (optional)

Terminal 1:

npm run dev

Terminal 2:

npm run type-check:watch

üßπ Auto-fix lint issues quickly
npm run lint:fix
